did.unittitle: General or Miscellaneous audiovisual materials

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. When requesting to view audiovisual material, please refer to the Title and the AV Number (example: AV 1916). Researchers are asked to check the "Restrictions" note for each Title. If a Title does not currently have an access copy, please contact a RAC archivist for further instruction.

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Materials note
separatedmaterial.p: The majority of audiovisual materials have been physically separated from an archival collection.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: In most cases, the specific details of the provenance are unknown.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This aggregation of miscellaneous audiovisual materials is an artificial collection created by the RAC in order to efficiently and effectively manage and present the miscellaneous moving images and audio materials held among our archival holdings.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The Rockefeller Archive Center recognizes that our audiovisual materials may contain problematic language and/or content.

The films, videos, and/or sound in this collection have not been altered in any way. All titles and/or content are illustrative of the creator's original vision. As such, this audiovisual collection may contain discriminatory visual and/or aural content that is representative of racial, gendered, or ableist biases.

Accompanying description, most often with creator or donor-generated language and terminology, has to this point been retained and maintained "as received" by RAC with minimal archivist intervention or augmentation.
We acknowledge these problems and aim to cultivate inclusive representation and equity by reconsidering and enhancing our description of this audiovisual material with current sensibilities.

accessrestrict.p: Open for research. When requesting to view audiovisual material, please refer to the Title and the AV Number (example: AV 1916). did.unittitle: St. Mihiel Drive

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Produced by the Signal Corps of the U.S. Army taken under action and service conditions in France. Film depicts General Pershing in his office; trucks and troops move up a road; artillery is fired; patrols cut through barbered wire; infantry advance behind tranks; DH-4 airplanes lined up on an airfield; artillery is moved, loaded, and fired; the infantry crosses captured enemy trenches; refugees are fed; POWs are hered to the rear. The St. Mihiel Drive was a World War I battle fought between September 12-15, 1918.

did.unittitle: The Effects of Morphine on Learned Adaptive Behavior and Experimental Neurosis in Cats
did.physdesc: Silent, Black & white, 6 minutes. Only available on original 16mm film.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Film from the Neurophysiology Laboratories and the Division of Psychiatry at the Otho S.A. Sprague Memorial Institute and the University of Chicago. Summary of experimental work by Jules H. Masserman, M.D., University of Chicago, and Adam Wikler, M.D., U.S. Public Health Service. Contains some graphic footage of experiments on cats in a laboratory setting.

did.unittitle: Vacationlands, U.S.A.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Digital access copy currently unavailable. Please contact a RAC archivist for further instruction.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Narrated by Arthur Godfrey. Warner Brothers tourism film showcasing Snake River, Grand Teton National Park, and includes behind-the-scenes filming of 1963 motion picture "Spencer's Mountain." Footage of actors Henry Fonda, Maureen O'Hara, and James MacArthur.
From American Film Institute (AFI) Catalog "Spencer's Mountain"(1963)

The 23 Apr 1963 "Daily Variety" reported that Warner Brothers planned to release a short subject, Vacationlands, U.S.A., to theaters free of charge. The film included sequences from Spencer's Mountain, along with additional footage of Grand Teton National Park
